  "structural_observations": [
    {
      "observation": "Total cash secular decline",
      "detail": "Total Cash has fallen from ~$234M (Sep 2022) to ~$89M (May 2026), a decline of ~$145M over 3.5 years. Unavailable cash has also fallen, but Available Cash as a percentage of Total Cash has remained roughly 3-8% throughout \u2014 suggesting the cash structure (unavailable vs available) has been broadly stable while the absolute pool shrinks."
    },
    {
      "observation": "Zero-forecast within 30 days is now structural",
      "detail": "Since mid-2023 (Jun 2023 BOD onward), EVERY single BOD model has shown Available Cash hitting zero within the 30-day near-term forecast window. This shifted from an occasional warning signal (Sep-Dec 2022) to a permanent baseline condition. It reflects that the company has been operationally cash-flow negative and dependent on non-recurring items (debt draws, asset sales, equity injections) to maintain any liquidity."
    },
    {
      "observation": "HTS facility not actively used in any reviewed file",
      "detail": "Available Cash = AC (No HTS) in every file analyzed. The HTS facility (appearing in the Cash Flow sheet header) does not appear to be actively drawing a differential between available and HTS-free cash. This means Available Cash figures reported are the true unrestricted available amount."
    },
    {
      "observation": "Rescue mechanism evolution",
      "detail": "2022: Equity offering draws ($120M Aug offering, $140M Jun offering) provided large one-time rescues. 2023 H1: Smaller term loan draws ($15-33M/month). Oct 2023: $173M debt injection (largest single rescue). 2024 onward: Smaller/irregular asset sales and term loan draws. 2025-2026: No large rescue mechanism visible \u2014 operating in sub-$5M available cash sustainably."
    },
    {
      "observation": "The Oct 18, 2023 injection ($137M+ to Available Cash) was the largest single-day liquidity event",
      "detail": "On Oct 18, 2023, Available Cash jumped from $9.67M to $146.93M \u2014 a +$137.3M increase. This corresponds to a $173.19M term loan/debt injection per the October 2023 Liquidity summary tab, net of concurrent disbursements. This single event prevented what would have been a complete liquidity failure, as the Sep 2023 model had been forecasting zero-avail as early as Sep 27."
    }
